  "id": "pop-jazz-v2/twelve-bar-blues-c-two-chorus",
  "labels": {
    "globalKey": "C:maj",
    "notes": "Two choruses of the 12-bar form, ending on a final tonic. Exists because the single-chorus fixture ends on the V7 turnaround: the cadence that identifies the blues tonic happens at the loop seam (bar 12's V7 resolving into the next chorus's I7), which a single pass never reaches. This is the realistic looping case; the single-chorus fixture stays as the documented edge."
  },
  "schema": "whatkey-fixture/1",
  "title": "12-bar blues in C, two choruses"
